title: Miami tops UBS' list of global cities at risk of a real estate bubble. Here's how other major US markets stack up.
content:
For the second straight year, Miami is at the top of the list of global cities most at risk of being in a real-estate bubble, according to UBS.
Earlier this week, the bank put out its annual Global Real Estate Bubble Index.
Cities that end up with an overall score above 1.5 are at "high" risk of being in a bubble, while those with a score of 1 to 1.49 are at "elevated" risk.
"By contrast, prices in cities with moderate or low risk fell roughly 5%, while rents and incomes were broadly flat," they continued.
Below are the four US markets on the list of 21 global cities, and where they fell on the list, starting with Miami.

title: Is Nvidia Recycling Profits?
content:
The gist of the story is that Nvidia is investing in its clients, who then use the funds to buy Nvidia chips.
However, the investment could prove damaging if OpenAI fails to produce profits; thus, it doesn’t need as many Nvidia chips as was initially expected.
The bottom left table shows that BB investors are only earning 1.39% more than AAA corporate bond investors.
When the COVID-19 pandemic shut down the global economy, BB-rated bond spreads rose from 1.90% to 7.52%.
A weakening economy should be a warning that default risks are rising, but corporate bond investors appear to be unconcerned.

title: Trump Tariffs May Not Hurt Indian Companies, Says Morgan Stanley: THIS Pharma Stock An Exception
content:
The tariff, which was announced by Donald Trump on Truth Social, will take effect from October 1, 2025.
Morgan Stanley believes the impact of this move could be limited, as far as the Indian market is concerned.
However, companies like Sun Pharma could be at risk due to their speciality drug presence in the US.
“Sun, among our coverage, is the only one with Speciality U.S. exposure but has a U.S. plant,” Morgan Stanley said, before admitting that the company's own domestic facility offers some protection.
As far as the other companies are concerned, Morgan Stanley sees minimal impact on firms like Lupin, Cipla, and Dr. Reddy’s Laboratories, as their business in the US is largely in the generic segment, which is exempt from tariffs, so far.

title: The Shortest Presidential Campaign
content:
Culture / Books & the Arts / The Shortest Presidential Campaign Kamala Harris’s 107 Days offers a devastating indictment of Joe Biden.
If presidents are stars on the stage of world history, vice presidents are nervous understudies hidden away behind the scenes.
The pathos of being a veep pervades Kamala Harris’s campaign memoir 107 Days.
It is, 107 Days argues, all his fault: Biden’s selfish decision to run for a second term despite his advanced age created a situation where Harris faced the impossible task of running a truncated campaign of 107 days.
In painting such a devastating picture of Biden, Harris raises questions about her own political judgment.

title: How to Party Like a Korean in the Middle of a Hurricane
content:
A sool party is literally just a party with alcohol, but the best Korean sool parties are hosted at home like this—more of a never-ending friend hang than a packed blowout party.
*Some tips & ideas for hosting your own sool party:Stock up on frozen Korean BBQ meats and accoutrements.
Korean BBQ has long been a mainstay of Korean food culture: a way for friends and family to gather and celebrate birthdays or job promotions, or just to have a good time.
It’s also worth sourcing Korean BBQ tongs—I love them not only for grilling but for cooking in general.
__________________________________From Soju Party How to Drink (and Eat!)
